<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb6a4d6a7-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s300ff–140"><num value="300ff–140">§ 300ff–140.</num><heading> Applicability of part</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">This part shall not apply in a State if the chief executive officer of the State certifies to the Secretary that the law of the State is substantially consistent with this part.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idb6a4d6a8-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/act/1944-07-01/ch373">July 1, 1944, ch. 373</ref>, title XXVI, § 2695I, as added <ref href="/us/pl/111/87/s13">Pub. L. 111–87, § 13</ref>, <date date="2009-10-30">Oct. 30, 2009</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/123/2903">123 Stat. 2903</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idb6a4d6a9-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idb6a4d6aa-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="idb6a4d6ab-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section effective as if enacted on <date date="2009-09-30">Sept. 30, 2009</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/111/87/s2/a/3/B">section 2(a)(3)(B) of Pub. L. 111–87</ref>, set out as an Effective Date of 2009 Amendment; Revival of Section note under <ref href="/us/usc/t42/s300ff–11">section 300ff–11 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
